      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "Your 7-segment button counter is ready! 🎉 Here's a full breakdown:\n\n---\n\n## 📌 Wiring Table\n\n| Arduino Pin | Component | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| **D2** | R_A → Segment A | Top bar |\n| **D3** | R_B → Segment B | Top-right |\n| **D4** | R_C → Segment C | Bottom-right |\n| **D5** | R_D → Segment D | Bottom bar |\n| **D6** | R_E → Segment E | Bottom-left |\n| **D7** | R_F → Segment F | Top-left |\n| **D8** | R_G → Segment G | Middle bar |\n| **GND** | Display common | Common cathode |\n| **D9** | Button (one side) | Increment input |\n| **GND** | Button (other side) | With internal pull-up |\n\nEach segment has a **220Ω series resistor** for current limiting.\n\n---\n\n## 🔢 How It Works\n\n- **Button press** is detected via `INPUT_PULLUP` — no external pull-up resistor needed.\n- A **30ms debounce delay** prevents false triggers from contact bounce.\n- Counter increments **0 → 1 → 2 → … → 9 → 0** (wraps around).\n- Digits are displayed using an `if/else` lookup table for each of the 7 segments.\n\n---\n\n## ⚡ Power Budget Summary\n\n| Item | Current |\n|---|---|\n| Each lit segment (5V − 2V) / 220Ω | ~13.6 mA |\n| Max segments ON at once (digit 8, all 7 lit) | ~95 mA |\n| Typical digit (avg ~4–5 segments) | ~55–68 mA |\n| Button pin | < 1 mA |\n| **Total draw** | **≤ ~96 mA** |\n\n> ✅ Each individual pin stays **well under 20mA** — each segment draws ~13.6mA. Total board draw is within the Arduino Uno's safe 500mA USB limit."
        }
      ]
    }
